From c6cdb34e4451f7de6e57c26aa953e25de4cd748c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ishan-parihar <ishanbestdabang@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Feb 2026 07:25:37 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat: Add OTG power fix and SukiSU for wireless mic receiver
 support

This patch enables USB OTG power output for devices that trigger
Debug Accessory Mode (Rd resistors on both CC pins), such as
wireless microphone receivers.

Changes:
- Type-C role: Set to SRC Only (role_def=2) to always provide power
- VCONN: Disabled to prevent overcurrent faults
- Debug Accessory Mode: Enable 5V/1500mA VBUS output
- USB Host: Trigger OTG host mode for debug accessory devices
- Legacy Cable Detection: Bypass to prevent disconnect loops
- SukiSU: Integrated for root support (builtin branch)

SukiSU Setup:
  git clone https://github.com/SukiSU-Ultra/SukiSU-Ultra.git KernelSU
  cd KernelSU && git checkout builtin
  cp -r kernel/* ../drivers/kernelsu/

Fixes: Wireless mic receiver not receiving power from OTG port
Tested: Jieli Technology USB Composite Device (wireless mic receiver)
Device: Xiaomi Redmi Note 8 Pro (begonia), MT6785 SoC
